I absolutely adore the view from up
here! It's as if I was inside a brilliant
gemstone!
18:
Hey, girl! Where'd you learn how to
fly like that?

I could ask the same of you! How do

24:
Hah, you're funny. You interested in

33:

"Edgeflying" professional, Breeze?
36:
Technically we're called "Edgeflyers",

bucks when we win, too. Edgeflying

37:
But it's more than that. The feeling of
the wind across your face, the thrill
of speeding down the track,
neck-and-neck... That's what I live
for.
39:
I see! You must truly love racing,
then.
42:
...Say, why don't you give it a try?
Rulebook says that you can use
anything, as long as it flies straight!
45:
I definitely want to see you race,
Zephyr.
49: Are you sure? Isn't it too late to enter?
51:
Why, of course you can! The more
contestants, the merrier.
53:
Breeze here is my top competitor.
Any friend of hers is more than
welcome to join. Isn't that right,
Breeze?
55: B-Boss, I... That's not what I meant!
58:
Um, excuse me... 
I do not think I quite understand.
61:
Edgeflying is still a VERY minor
sport... So, we've been looking for
ways to grow our audience, you see.
62:
To do that, we need a compelling

65:
And so... you are asking me to let
Breeze win? 
THAT is your "compelling story"?
68:
I'm so sorry! I totally understand 
if you don't want to do it!
70:
It's just... I need this win. Without the
viewership, these races won't last.
And that's not gonna make anyone
happy...
73:
I see your point... 
and I think I understand.
77:
But I would rather be true to myself
and fly these neon skies without any
reservations. The same way we flew
only moments ago.
80:
...Is that not why you invited me to
race?
83:
Well, if you're still interested, feel free
to contact me. You will be paid
handsomely, of course.
89:
I must do something about this.
Though, I am not sure if it is for her
benefit...
93:
Then, maybe we can lend you a
hand?
98:
Welcome everyone, to the
Edgeflying championship finale!
Can superstar racer Breeze defend
her six-race winning streak? 
Let's get ready to find out!
100:
I'm sorry, Zephyr... I wish we could've
had a real race.
103:
...Why don't we? Are you afraid that
you might lose?
107: On your marks... Get set... GO!
112:
Come on, Breeze! Show me what
you are truly capable of!
115:
You're on! Get ready to eat my dust,
girl!
130: You were very fast. Super fast.
136:
What the HELL are you two thinking?!
We're about to lose what little
audience we have left!
140:
Have no fear! I have a feeling that
plenty of people will start paying
attention to Edgeflying. Isn't that
right, Alk?
143:
K-King Johnson, the CEO of PBC?!
And a representative of the Noxel
Group? Seriously?!
145:
An introduction, from one of Alk's
dear friends! We told them about
Edgeflying, and they seemed rather
interested in the sport.
148:
So much so that they are willing to
invest in it! So long as the marketing
is done well, they expect Edgeflying
to be the next big thing!
151:
Zephyr, I... I can't believe it. 
You did all of this?
154:
You opened up a new sky for me
today. And for that, I thank you,
Breeze. I will be looking forward to
our next race!
157: ...Yeah! And next time, I won't lose!
161:
It sounds like you've had quite the
adventure, my lady.
164:
Indeed I have! The world is ever-so
large... and I have experienced both
luck and misfortune on my journey.
171:
...I want to be a helping hand to
those less fortunateâ€”a wind of
fortune that can carry them soaring

174:
Well! I'm sure the Chief will be
pleased to hear that. Now, let's go
back to the village andâ€”
176:
Forgive me, but I shall not be
returning yet.
182:
There are still so many skies that 
I have yet to explore!
185:
I will be sure to bring you home a
present! So, farewell!
188: I... I don't know what I was expecting.
191:
Hah, sorry about that. 
Give the Chief our regards, eh?
195: Come, join me. New worlds await!
